sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1375031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a long part with K1375000 and pBAD with CinR/I system
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zheng Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I761014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The RBS (BBa_B0034) was combined with cinr (BBa_C0077), cinl (BBa_C0076) and D-term (BBa_B0014) to create a single transcription control device for BBa_R0078
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Comparing to BBa_I761000, double terminator is added in the end of this construct
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chih-Hsien Yang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1375000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a Constitutive promoter that product araC protein, it will reduce the pBAD expression, unless the arabinose has been added.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We can use this part to make a gene sequence to produce some protein regulated by arabinose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zheng Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0012 and BBa_B0011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I761000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is intended to be used as an transcription activator for BBa_R0078. It can be used to control the expression of the gene downstream of BBa_R0078.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The RBS (BBa_B0034) was combined with CinR (BBa_C0077) and HSL (BBa_C0076) to create a single transcription control device for BBa_R0078.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: 2007 NYMU_Taiwan iGEM Team

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I13458
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: promoter C and arabinose C operon
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PC and AraC from the AraBAD operator. PC and AraC are on the complementary strand, reading right to left.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Michener

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from luxICDABEG operon terminator of Vibrio fischeri <genbank>AF170104</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Bidirectional transcriptional terminator consisting of a 22 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In the naturally-occuring sequence there is a mismatch in the stem of the stem loop. This can be corrected via an A->G mutation (at position 40 -- sequence coordinate/not MFOLD coordinate). The above sequence does not reflect this mutation (but the MFOLD image does). This terminator's location cannot be found using some inverted repeat detectors like PALINDROME because it is too short and contains a mismatch. This one was found with the help of Tom Knight. It lies between two coding regions that point towards eachother.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cinI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: cinI codes for an autoinducer synthetase which utilizes SAM to make O3-C14:1-HSL. In complex with O3-C14:1-HSL, CinR (BBa_C0077) binds to the Cin promoter (BBa_R0077) and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The regulatory locus cinRI in Rhizobium leguminosarum conrols a network of quorum-sensing loci Lithgow, JK; Wilkinson, A; Hardman, A; Rodelas, B; Wisniewski-Dye, F; Williams, P; Downie, AJ MOL. MICROBIOLOGY 37(1): 81-97, 2000

Change log: original STOP: tga -> tAaTAA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: crackdots

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cinr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In complex with O3-C14:1-HSL (made by BBa_C0076), CinR binds to the Cin promoter (BBa_R0077) and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The regulatory locus cinRI in Rhizobium leguminosarum conrols a network of quorum-sensing loci Lithgow, JK; Wilkinson, A; Hardman, A; Rodelas, B; Wisniewski-Dye, F; Williams, P; Downie, AJ MOL. MICROBIOLOGY 37(1): 81-97, 2000
